46 // This structure uniquely identifies a basic block section. ----
47 // Possible values are ----
48 // {Type: Default, Number: (unsigned)} (These are regular section IDs) ----
49 // {Type: Exception, Number: 0} (ExceptionSectionID) ----
50 // {Type: Cold, Number: 0} (ColdSectionID) ----
51 struct MBBSectionID { ----
52 enum SectionType { ----
53 Default = 0, // Regular section (these sections are distinguished by the ----
54 // Number field). ----
55 Exception, // Special section type for exception handling blocks ----
56 Cold, // Special section type for cold blocks ----
57 } Type; ----
58 unsigned Number; ----
59 ----
60 MBBSectionID(unsigned N) : Type(Default), Number(N) {} 10 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
61 ----
62 // Special unique sections for cold and exception blocks. ----
63 const static MBBSectionID ColdSectionID; ----
64 const static MBBSectionID ExceptionSectionID; ----
65 ----
66 bool operator==(const MBBSectionID &Other) const { 0
67 return Type == Other.Type && Number == Other.Number; 0
68 } ----
69 ----
70 bool operator!=(const MBBSectionID &Other) const { return !(*this == Other); } 0
71 ----
72 private: ----
73 // This is only used to construct the special cold and exception sections. ----
74 MBBSectionID(SectionType T) : Type(T), Number(0) {} 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
75 }; ----

469 class liveout_iterator { ----
470 public: ----
471 using iterator_category = std::input_iterator_tag; ----
472 using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t; ----
473 using value_type = RegisterMaskPair; ----
474 using pointer = const RegisterMaskPair *; ----
475 using reference = const RegisterMaskPair &; ----
476 ----
477 liveout_iterator(const MachineBasicBlock &MBB, MCPhysReg ExceptionPointer, 0
478 MCPhysReg ExceptionSelector, bool End) ----
479 : ExceptionPointer(ExceptionPointer), 0
480 ExceptionSelector(ExceptionSelector), BlockI(MBB.succ_begin()), 0
481 BlockEnd(MBB.succ_end()) { 0
482 if (End) 0
483 BlockI = BlockEnd; 0
484 else if (BlockI != BlockEnd) { 0
485 LiveRegI = (*BlockI)->livein_begin(); 0
486 if (!advanceToValidPosition()) 0
487 return; 0
488 if (LiveRegI->PhysReg == ExceptionPointer || 0
489 LiveRegI->PhysReg == ExceptionSelector) 0
490 ++(*this); 0
491 } ----
492 } ----
493 ----
494 liveout_iterator &operator++() { 0
495 do { ----
496 ++LiveRegI; 0
497 if (!advanceToValidPosition()) 0
498 return *this; 0
499 } while ((*BlockI)->isEHPad() && 0
500 (LiveRegI->PhysReg == ExceptionPointer || 0
501 LiveRegI->PhysReg == ExceptionSelector)); 0
502 return *this; 0
503 } ----
504 ----
505 liveout_iterator operator++(int) { ----
506 liveout_iterator Tmp = *this; ----
507 ++(*this); ----
508 return Tmp; ----
509 } ----
510 ----
511 reference operator*() const { ----
512 return *LiveRegI; ----
513 } ----
514 ----
515 pointer operator->() const { ----
516 return &*LiveRegI; ----
517 } ----
518 ----
519 bool operator==(const liveout_iterator &RHS) const { ----
520 if (BlockI != BlockEnd) ----
521 return BlockI == RHS.BlockI && LiveRegI == RHS.LiveRegI; ----
522 return RHS.BlockI == BlockEnd; ----
523 } ----
524 ----
525 bool operator!=(const liveout_iterator &RHS) const { ----
526 return !(*this == RHS); ----
527 } ----
528 private: ----
529 bool advanceToValidPosition() { 0
530 if (LiveRegI != (*BlockI)->livein_end()) 0
531 return true; 0
532 ----
533 do { ----
534 ++BlockI; 0
535 } while (BlockI != BlockEnd && (*BlockI)->livein_empty()); 0
536 if (BlockI == BlockEnd) 0
537 return false; 0
538 ----
539 LiveRegI = (*BlockI)->livein_begin(); 0

858 /// Returns an iterator to the first non-debug instruction in the basic block, ----
859 /// or end(). Skip any pseudo probe operation if \c SkipPseudoOp is true. ----
860 /// Pseudo probes are like debug instructions which do not turn into real ----
861 /// machine code. We try to use the function to skip both debug instructions ----
862 /// and pseudo probe operations to avoid API proliferation. This should work ----
863 /// most of the time when considering optimizing the rest of code in the ----
864 /// block, except for certain cases where pseudo probes are designed to block ----
865 /// the optimizations. For example, code merge like optimizations are supposed ----
866 /// to be blocked by pseudo probes for better AutoFDO profile quality. ----
867 /// Therefore, they should be considered as a valid instruction when this ----
868 /// function is called in a context of such optimizations. On the other hand, ----
869 /// \c SkipPseudoOp should be true when it's used in optimizations that ----
870 /// unlikely hurt profile quality, e.g., without block merging. The default ----
871 /// value of \c SkipPseudoOp is set to true to maximize code quality in ----
872 /// general, with an explict false value passed in in a few places like branch ----
873 /// folding and if-conversion to favor profile quality. ----
874 iterator getFirstNonDebugInstr(bool SkipPseudoOp = true); ----
875 const_iterator getFirstNonDebugInstr(bool SkipPseudoOp = true) const { ----
876 return const_cast(this)->getFirstNonDebugInstr( ----
877 SkipPseudoOp); ----
878 } ----
